Postman -> Postman is an API testing tool used to send HTTP requests, validate responses, and perform manual API testing before automation.
  
Workspace -> Create a workspace where we can create collection, env etc 
Collection -> contains number of folders & HTTP request

Validation Point
1. Status code
2. Time
3. Response Body
4. Cookies & Header

HTTP Methods (Very Important)
Commonly Used Methods
Method	                Purpose	                    Real Example
GET	                    Fetch data	                Get user details
POST	                Create new data	            Create new user
PUT	                    Update full data	        Update user profile
PATCH	                Partial update	            Update email only
DELETE	                Remove data	                Delete user

HTTP Status
2xx -> Success               
200 - OK
201 - Created  
204 - No content

4xx -> Client Error
400 - Bad Request
401 - Unauthorized -> Authentication is missing or invalid
403 - Forbidden -> Authentication is valid, but access is denied
404 - Not found

5xx -> Server Error
500 - Internal Server Error
502 - Bad Gateway
503 - Service Unavaiable

HTTP Headers -> provides metadata about request/response

Common Request Headers
Header	                Purpose
Content-Type	        Data format (JSON/XML)
Authorization	        Token / credentials
Accept	                Expected response format
Common Response Headers

Header	                Purpose
Content-Type	        Response format
Cache-Control	        Caching rules
Server	                Server info

Difference between status code

204 No Content vs 404 Not found
204(No content) -> The request was successfully processed, but there is no response body to return.
404(Not found)  -> The requested resource does not exist on the server.

401 Unauthorised vs 403 Forbidden
401(unathorised) -> Authentication is missing or invalid
403(forbidden)   -> Authentication is valid but access is denied

